Notice of Financial Incentive
We offer customers the ability to participate in a registration program ("Program"). Depending on your state of residence, the Program may be considered a financial incentive or loyalty program. Participation in the Program is entirely voluntary. If you would like to participate in the Program, please opt-in by signing up. If you sign up, you will receive:
Access to article and newsletter content on POLITICO.com and the POLITICO mobile application (collectively, “POLITICO Content”). You will also receive an exclusive email newsletter offered only to registered users.
When you decide to participate in the Program, we will collect your email address, job title, and employer (depending on which you voluntarily provide to us) (collectively, "Registration Information"). Registration Information may also be disclosed to service providers or other providers or partners that support our operational business purposes. By voluntarily opting in to this Program, you will receive free access to POLITICO Content and an exclusive email newsletter, and you may also receive content from us through emails.
Depending on your state of residence, if you decide you no longer wish to participate in the Program, you may withdraw at any time. You may exercise this right to withdraw using the following method, depending on the information you have provided to us:
Email webin@politico.com to request withdrawal from the Program, using the same email address you used for registration. To process your withdrawal request, we will need to delete your account. Before deleting your account to honor your withdrawal request, we will send you an email requesting that you explicitly acknowledge and confirm your decision to delete your account. This step is essential to ensure that the account deletion aligns with your intentions and helps mitigate unauthorized actions. Once we receive your confirmation, your account will be deleted, and you will be withdrawn from the Program.  You may also unsubscribe from our newsletters at any time by visiting our Preferences page or by clicking “unsubscribe” at the bottom of the email. Visit the
FAQ
page for more information.
We estimate that the value of your data is equal to the value of the subscription to our services. Registration Information enables us to deliver personalized content, offers, subscription services, and value to you, which enables us to establish a relationship with you, and is valued by us in order to facilitate a positive customer experience. In determining the value of the Registration Information, we consider the profit generated from our advertising partners that includes personal information, which is reasonably correlated to the value provided to you through personalized content, discounts, or offers.
International Data Transfers
We are based in the United States. Any information you provide to us through use of the Services may be stored and processed, transferred between, and accessed from the United States and other countries which may not guarantee the same level of protection of personal information as the one in which you reside. We may need to send your personal information overseas as part of our normal business operations. Provided the data protection laws of these other countries differ from those in the United States, please be assured that we take reasonable steps to ensure that your privacy is protected.
Shine the Light Disclosure
We do not disclose personal information as defined by California Civil Code § 1798.83 (the “Shine the Light Law”) with third parties, other than our affiliates, for their direct marketing purposes absent your consent. If you are a California resident, you may request information about our compliance with the Shine the Light Law by sending an email to privacy@politico.com or by sending a letter to 1000 Wilson Blvd, 8
th
Floor, Arlington, VA 22209. Any such request must include “Request for California Privacy Information” in the subject line and include your name, street address, city, state, and ZIP code. Please note that we are only required to respond to one request per customer each year, and we are not required to respond to requests made by means other than through the email address or mailing address referenced above.
Updates to the Policy
We may update this policy from time to time. To the extent permitted by law, any changes to our Privacy Policy will be posted to the websites and will become effective upon posting. Any changes will be effective only after the effective date of the change and will not affect any dispute arising prior to the effective date of the change.
